name: UInterchangeAnimationTrackNode
doc:
Class to represent an animation on the property of a camera, light, or scene node
The list of supported properties is enumerated in EInterchangeAnimatedProperty.

methods.name: GetCustomActorDependencyUid
methods.doc: Get the actor dependency to this object.

methods.name: GetCustomAnimationPayloadKey
methods.doc: Get the payload key needed to retrieve the animation for this track.

methods.name: GetCustomFrameCount
methods.doc: Get the number of frames for the animation of this track.

methods.name: SetCustomActorDependencyUid
methods.doc: Set the actor dependency to this object.

methods.name: SetCustomAnimationPayloadKey
methods.doc: Set the payload key needed to retrieve the animation for this track.

methods.name: SetCustomFrameCount
methods.doc: Set the number of frames for the animation of this track.

methods.name: SetCustomPropertyTrack
methods.doc: Set the property animated by this track. Usually the name of a UMovieSceneTrack, e.g for UMovieSceneColorTrack -> Color
